Isn't the following enough?
```cpp
FILE* file = fsbridge::fopen(path, fReadOnly ? "rb": "ab+");
if (!file) {
    LogPrintf("Unable to open file %s\n", path.string());
    return nullptr;
}
```
Why the second attempt when it's not read only?

